**Parks and Recreation:** Lucknow boasts numerous parks and [recreation](/Recreation) areas managed by the Lucknow Development Authority. These include the [Kukrail Reserve Forest](/Kukrail_Reserve_Forest), [Qaisar Bagh](/Qaisar_Bagh), Gomti Riverfront Park, [Dr. Ram Manohar Lohia Park, Gomti Nagar](/Dr._Ram_Manohar_Lohia_Park,_Gomti_Nagar), Eco Park, [Ambedkar Memorial Park](/Ambedkar_Memorial_Park), and [Janeshwar Mishra Park, Lucknow](/Janeshwar_Mishra_Park,_Lucknow), which is recognized as the largest park in [Asia](/Asia). Other recreational spaces include Buddha Park and Hathi Park. These areas feature lush greenery, artificial lakes, India's longest cycling and jogging tracks, and diverse flora. Plans are also in motion to install a large Ferris wheel within Janeshwar Mishra Park, inspired by the London Eye, offering panoramic city views. Kukrail Picnic Spot, a crocodile-breeding sanctuary located near Indiranagar, is Asia's largest center for crocodile breeding and, along with a small zoo and ample open space, offers a unique recreational experience.

**Sister Cities:** Lucknow shares a sister city relationship with [Brisbane](/Brisbane), [Queensland](/Queensland), [Australia](/Australia).

